title: Grateful Dead Live at Red Rocks Amphitheater on 1987-08-12
description:
Disc One/Set One:
Hell in a Bucket
Sugaree
Good Times
Cumberland Blues
Mexicali Blues
Friend of the Devil
Dead Air
My Brother Esau
Bird Song
The Music Never Stopped

Disc Two/Set Two:
China Cat
I Know You Rider
Women are Smarter
Terrapin Station
Drums

Disc Three/Set Two cont:
Space
The Other One
Dear Mr Fantasy
Wharf Rat
Lovelight
E: Mighty Quinn

reviews.review_text:
Wharf Rat! Thanx Tony for making this available!  I don't think I have heard this since the show.
The sound is clear, nice vocals, you can hear Phil thunder, plenty of guitar and keys.  There is some hiss but not very noticeable when they are playing.
1st set has a strong, but a bit short, Sugaree.  A solid Good Times featurs a Brent scat vocal.  Brent is singing great tonight.  The only pairing of Cumberland into Mexicali is a treat.  Bird Song has a powerful jam and Music finishes the set strong.
2nd set has a real nice China/Rider.  The Other One comes out of space slowly and features a quiet 1st verse.  I think the highlight of the show is the Wharf Rat.  Upon inspection, it might be the best I have attended.  Real strong when need be, particularly at the end, but with real delicate vocal work, especially the coda.
You can fit each set onto one CD.
Give this a listen, you might like it.  Peace

Good Times! I give the show a 3 on recording and transferring yet, the material is awesome! Brent is on Jerry is sounding wonferdul and bobby and the boys are rockin it out with some great vibes! The song Good Times is really the song "Never Trust a Woman". Lord, ain't it true!
 Love y'all all! bors nd sis alike!
